be turned.

965
01:22:17,492 --> 01:22:18,822
Everyone you've
ever known,

966
01:22:19,322 --> 01:22:22,032
everyone you've ever
fucking loved.

967
01:22:22,542 --> 01:22:23,992
It won't matter
who's pureblood

968
01:22:24,582 --> 01:22:25,752
and who's not.

969
01:22:26,162 --> 01:22:28,792
How are you gonna cure
the whole fuckin' world?

970
01:22:30,502 --> 01:22:32,042
Hmm?

971
01:22:35,592 --> 01:22:37,592
And Blade's blood
is the key.

972
01:22:38,132 --> 01:22:39,722
We got an intruder.

973
01:23:08,842 --> 01:23:09,762
Deac, I don't think
you understand.

974
01:23:10,182 --> 01:23:11,092
I mean, this dude
is fuckin' bad. What?

975
01:23:11,552 --> 01:23:13,222
He's, like, he had
20 guys around him-

976
01:23:13,682 --> 01:23:15,062
and he's got shit
he throws at you-

977
01:23:15,512 --> 01:23:16,722
Yeah, the swords.

978
01:23:17,182 --> 01:23:18,102
Throw it in the air,
catch it underneath.

979
01:23:18,482 --> 01:23:19,812
Yeah. Shut the fuck up!

980
01:23:20,272 --> 01:23:21,272
There's no
intruder where we are.

981
01:23:21,732 --> 01:23:23,152
Look, make it happen,
all right?

982
01:23:23,562 --> 01:23:24,732
It's one guy on foot.

983
01:23:29,402 --> 01:23:30,992
That's him!
Get him!

984
01:23:50,512 --> 01:23:52,132
Why am I hearing
gunfire? Huh?

985
01:23:52,472 --> 01:23:54,892
Did I tell anybody
to start shooting?

986
01:23:55,352 --> 01:23:56,392
I need him alive.

987
01:23:56,722 --> 01:23:57,892
No!

988
01:24:00,522 --> 01:24:02,482
Please!

989
01:24:02,942 --> 01:24:04,062
I just work for them!

990
01:24:06,412 --> 01:24:07,912
Jesus Christ.
Lock this place down.

991
01:24:08,372 --> 01:24:09,372
Yes, sir!

992
01:24:46,202 --> 01:24:48,372
Aah!

993
01:24:48,832 --> 01:24:50,952
Aieee!
Aah!

994
01:25:56,702 --> 01:25:58,362
Eric?

995
01:26:09,582 --> 01:26:11,132
But you died.

996
01:26:12,502 --> 01:26:14,562
I came back, Eric.

997
01:26:15,022 --> 01:26:16,352
That very same night...

998
01:26:18,192 --> 01:26:20,602
when Deacon welcomed me
into his arms.

999
01:26:28,702 --> 01:26:30,492
Uhh!

1000
01:26:37,622 --> 01:26:40,172
Jesus Christ. I thought
you'd be happy.

1001
01:26:40,622 --> 01:26:41,672
You're finally being
reunited with your mother,

1002
01:26:42,132 --> 01:26:43,422
and you act like this?

1003
01:26:45,212 --> 01:26:47,132
Blade, give it up.
It's over.

1004
01:26:47,552 --> 01:26:49,302
She belongs to me,
buddy.

1005
01:26:49,682 --> 01:26:50,762
Uh! Uhh!

1006
01:26:52,682 --> 01:26:53,802
Don't look so surprised.

1007
01:26:54,262 --> 01:26:55,512
You spent your whole life

1008
01:26:56,102 --> 01:26:58,482
looking for the vampire
who bit your mother.

1009
01:26:58,932 --> 01:27:00,852
Well, here I am.

1010
01:27:03,152 --> 01:27:04,062
Who would ever guess

1011
01:27:04,522 --> 01:27:06,612
you'd survive
your mother's death?

1012
01:27:07,112 --> 01:27:08,032
But you did.

1013
01:27:08,442 --> 01:27:09,652
And here we are-

1014
01:27:10,112 --> 01:27:12,492
one big happy
fuckin' family.

1015
01:27:23,932 --> 01:27:25,602
I need my serum.

1016
01:27:28,352 --> 01:27:29,272
Maybe when we
get outta this,

1017
01:27:29,682 --> 01:27:31,522
I'll take that
miracle cure of yours.

1018
01:27:31,982 --> 01:27:33,562
There's one catch.

1019
01:27:37,522 --> 01:27:39,072
If it works,

1020
01:27:39,532 --> 01:27:40,442
you'll lose
your strength

1021
01:27:40,902 --> 01:27:44,912
and your ability
to regenerate.

1022
01:27:45,372 --> 01:27:47,332
You'll be
completely human.

1023
01:28:08,562 --> 01:28:09,562
Uhh!

1024
01:28:49,272 --> 01:28:51,612
Blade, Karen,

1025
01:28:52,032 --> 01:28:53,612
glad you could make it.

1026
01:28:54,072 --> 01:28:56,362
Hey, man. Thanks
for the shades.

1027
01:28:57,702 --> 01:28:59,782
Our ancestors
called this place

1028
01:29:00,202 --> 01:29:02,452
the Temple
of Eternal Night.

1029
01:29:05,582 --> 01:29:07,122
Nice, isn't it?

1030
01:29:07,502 --> 01:29:10,002
Apparently, these geniuses
forgot it ever existed.

1031
01:29:10,542 --> 01:29:12,842
Fortunately for us...

1032
01:29:13,342 --> 01:29:14,342
I'm what you
might call a...

1033
01:29:14,762 --> 01:29:17,302
student of history.

1034
01:29:30,662 --> 01:29:32,702
Why are we here?

1035
01:29:34,292 --> 01:29:38,332
This temple was built
for one glorious moment-

1036
01:29:38,792 --> 01:29:42,132
this night,
for the Blood God.

1037
01:29:50,392 --> 01:29:51,642
Thanks.

1038
01:29:56,982 --> 01:29:58,522
Let's see
this sword of yours.

1039
01:30:01,022 --> 01:30:03,192
Well.

1040
01:30:03,612 --> 01:30:04,322
Titanium, right?

1041
01:30:04,822 --> 01:30:06,742
Acid-etched?

1042
01:30:08,612 --> 01:30:11,282
I'll get used
to a weapon like this.

1043
01:30:17,042 --> 01:30:17,662
What?

1044
01:30:18,162 --> 01:30:20,582
You look surprised.

1045
01:30:21,132 --> 01:30:22,332
I told you, Blade,

1046
01:30:22,632 --> 01:30:24,632
I know everything
about you.

1047
01:30:25,712 --> 01:30:26,842
Hold out your arm,
Quinn.

1048
01:30:27,302 --> 01:30:28,092
Why, man?

1049
01:30:28,472 --> 01:30:29,172
These are-they're,
like, all better.

1050
01:30:29,602 --> 01:30:30,522
Hold out your arm.

1051
01:30:30,982 --> 01:30:31,982
Now.

1052
01:30:36,032 --> 01:30:37,072
Deac, I-

1053
01:30:42,322 --> 01:30:43,322
Just kidding.

1054
01:30:45,532 --> 01:30:47,202
Ha ha ha ha! He was fuckin' with me.

1055
01:30:47,622 --> 01:30:48,912
He was, like,
fuckin'...

1056
01:30:49,462 --> 01:30:50,002
Blade.

1057
01:30:50,502 --> 01:30:52,422
Blade.

1058
01:30:52,882 --> 01:30:53,582
He can't hear you,
honey.

1059
01:30:53,962 --> 01:30:55,592
The thirst has
got him now.

1060
01:31:01,302 --> 01:31:03,092
What do we have here?

1061
01:31:03,552 --> 01:31:05,972
The precious serum.

1062
01:31:06,352 --> 01:31:09,812
Mm. How long's it been
since you shot up?

1063
01:31:10,272 --> 01:31:12,652
12, 13 hours maybe?

1064
01:31:13,152 --> 01:31:14,982
I bet you're just
dying for a drink,

1065
01:31:15,522 --> 01:31:16,652
aren't you?

1066
01:31:19,152 --> 01:31:20,362
What's it feel like?

1067
01:31:22,362 --> 01:31:23,912
Is your blood on fire?

1068
01:31:24,322 --> 01:31:26,332
Try some.

1069
01:31:26,832 --> 01:31:29,082
You might like it.

1070
01:31:29,502 --> 01:31:31,542
Thanks, but I prefer
the real thing.

1071
01:31:32,082 --> 01:31:33,932
In any event,

1072
01:31:34,432 --> 01:31:36,472
I don't think you'll be
needing these any more.

1073
01:31:43,892 --> 01:31:45,312
It's a shame, you know?

1074
01:31:46,612 --> 01:31:47,902
When I think of what
you've become,

1075
01:31:48,322 --> 01:31:50,612
what you should
have become.

1076
01:31:51,072 --> 01:31:52,702
I guess
I don't blame you.

1077
01:31:53,112 --> 01:31:54,452
I mean, with everything
that's happened,

1078
01:31:54,992 --> 01:31:55,952
it's the human
side of you

1079
01:31:56,412 --> 01:31:57,662
